{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluation for Generative Document Retrieval5.1.1 Metrics.",
    "In this section, we discuss several core metrics for evaluating Generative Retrieval (GR) methods.",
    "These metrics provide different perspectives on the effectiveness of a GR system, including its accuracy, efficiency, and the relevance of its results.",
    "Specifically, we consider Recall, R-Precision, Mean Reciprocal Rank (MRR), Mean Average Precision (MAP), and Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain (nDCG).",
    "Each metric captures unique aspects of retrieval performance, allowing for a comprehensive assessment of the system's capabilities.• Recall measures the proportion of relevant documents retrieved by the search system, reflecting its ability to find all relevant items."
  ]
}